					count: 2
				}
			]
		}
		{
			title: "Electrolysis"
			icon: "gtceu:lv_electrolyzer"
			x: -4d
			y: -2d
			description: ["The LV Electrolyzer passes a direct current through dissolved compounds to break them into constituent elements. Water becomes hydrogen and oxygen. Salt becomes sodium and chlorine. Alumina yields aluminum. Electrolysis is the only way to produce many pure elements in quantity — especially hydrogen, which is the universal GTCEu chemical feedstock and fuel source. Every electrolyzer you build will run continuously."]
			dependencies: ["NC01000000000002"]
			id: "NC01000000000003"
			tasks: [{
				id: "NC02000000000003"
				type: "item"
				item: "gtceu:lv_electrolyzer"
			}]
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "NC03000000000003"
					type: "item"
					item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
					count: 2
				}
			]
		}
		{
			title: "Spin Down"
			icon: "gtceu:lv_centrifuge"
			x: -4d
			y: -1d
			description: ["The LV Centrifuge uses high rotational speed to separate mixture components by density. It is used for ore purification — centrifuging crushed ore to recover byproduct dusts — and for separating gas mixtures, processing biomass into methane, and dozens of other reactions where density differences allow separation. Many GTCEu ore-processing lines route through a Centrifuge at the dust-washing step to recover additional byproducts that would otherwise be lost."]
			dependencies: ["NC01000000000002"]
			id: "NC01000000000004"
			tasks: [{
				id: "NC02000000000004"
				type: "item"
				item: "gtceu:lv_centrifuge"
			}]
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "NC03000000000004"
					type: "item"
					item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
					count: 2
				}
			]
		}
		{
			title: "Chemical Bath"
			icon: "gtceu:lv_chemical_bath"
			x: -4d
			y: 0d
			description: ["The LV Chemical Bath immerses items in a fluid reagent to chemically treat them. The primary use case is ore washing: bath crushed ores in Sodium Persulfate to recover extra dust byproducts before smelting, adding roughly 10% yield per ore. Chemical Baths also dye items, apply coatings, and perform other surface reactions. Building one alongside your ore processing line is a straightforward early efficiency upgrade that pays for itself within minutes of operation."]
			dependencies: ["NC01000000000002"]
			id: "NC01000000000005"
			tasks: [{
				id: "NC02000000000005"
				type: "item"
				item: "gtceu:lv_chemical_bath"
			}]
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "NC03000000000005"
					type: "item"
					item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
					count: 2
				}
			]
		}
		{
			title: "Higher Voltage Chemistry"
			icon: "gtceu:hv_chemical_reactor"
			x: -4d
			y: 1d
			description: ["Some chemical reactions require higher EU/t to drive — more energetic bond-breaking, more heat, more precision. The MV and HV Chemical Reactors handle these recipes, unlocking key plastics, solvents, and advanced chemical chains that feed into EV-tier circuits and beyond. Upgrade your Chemical Reactor as your power generation scales; each voltage tier simply has access to a broader recipe set, so nothing you have built becomes obsolete."]
			dependencies: ["NC01000000000002"]
			id: "NC01000000000006"
			tasks: [
				{
