					count: 2
				}
			]
		}
		{
			title: "High Octane"
			icon: "gtceu:high_octane_gasoline_bucket"
			x: -1d
			y: 3d
			description: ["High Octane Gasoline is the apex petroleum fuel, produced by multi-step refining of cracked naphtha through catalytic reforming reactions in the Chemical Reactor chain. It provides the highest EU/t per bucket among fossil fuels when burned in Gas Turbines and combustion engines. The production chain is lengthy and demands consistent chemical reactor throughput, making it a late oil-refinery milestone rather than a quick upgrade. Reaching this point means your refinery is a genuine chemical plant with multiple parallel processing lines."]
			dependencies: ["NC01000000000014"]
			id: "NC01000000000015"
			tasks: [{
				id: "NC02000000000020"
				type: "item"
				item: "gtceu:high_octane_gasoline_bucket"
